Are you passionate about pushing the boundaries of precision engineering? Do you thrive in an environment where innovation, complexity, and technical ownership come together?




About The Member Company
We are a global high\-tech consultancy company with a team of entrepreneurial engineers, scientists, and digital experts from around the world. Together we form a fast\-growing and proud community. We offer consultancy services to high\-profile clients globally in diverse service areas, such as:


* Technology \& Engineering
* Energy \& Renewables
* Life sciences \& Pharma
* Digital \& IT
**About this vacancy**
----------------------


As a Senior Mechatronics Engineer, you will take technical ownership of one or more highly complex subsystems, guiding their development from concept and design through industrialization and volume production.


You will work closely with System Architects, System Engineers, Project Managers, and multidisciplinary engineering teams to ensure technical excellence while balancing performance, reliability, manufacturability, and cost.


What will you do?

* Translate high\-level system requirements into subsystem concepts, functional architectures, and engineering specifications;
* take technical ownership of the development and realization of critical high\-precision modules and subsystems;
* drive design decisions related to motion systems, sensing technologies, actuators, control strategies, and system integration;
* lead technical trade\-offs between performance, reliability, manufacturability, scalability, and cost;
* collaborate with multidisciplinary teams across mechanics, electronics, software, controls, and system engineering;
* define and maintain the technology roadmap for your subsystem, ensuring alignment with future product and customer requirements;
* guide and coach engineers within project teams through design reviews, simulations, testing activities, and technical problem\-solving;
* support validation, integration, industrialization, and successful release of new designs into production;
* ensure that technical risks are identified early and effectively mitigated throughout the development process.


**What we expect from you**
---------------------------


* MSc or PhD degree in Mechatronics, Mechanical Engineering, Control Engineering, or a related technical discipline;
* minimum of 5 years of relevant industry experience, with a proven track record in the architecture and development of complex mechatronic systems or high\-precision modules;
* strong expertise in areas such as motion control, dynamics and vibration analysis, sensing and actuation technologies, system modelling, and precision engineering;
* hands\-on experience leading multidisciplinary development projects throughout the entire product lifecycle, from concept design to industrialization and release;
* excellent communication and technical leadership skills, with the ability to align stakeholders and drive critical engineering decisions;
* proficiency in modelling, simulation, and data analysis tools such as MATLAB, Simulink, FEM software, and Python;
* fluent in English, both written and spoken;
* currently living in the Netherlands.
**What you can expect from us**
-------------------------------


TMC is an international high\-tech consultancy company that brings expertise to its clients in order to support them with the realization of their technological challenges. As such, TMC is operating as an expert center at the disposition of its clients and we help them to be more competitive in an ever more global and faster\-changing technological world. At TMC we believe that people are the driving force behind technological innovation. That is why we want to create the best possible conditions for tech talents to thrive in. We offer you a challenging and stimulating work environment in which you can be the director of your own career. As an Employeneur you are part of our TMC family. Next to our outstanding technical expertise, fun and engagement are meaningful parts of our culture. \#LI\-AV6

Na Sourcing Trust, comprometemo\-nos a fornecer soluções tecnológicas inovadoras, fiáveis e personalizadas que capacitam as empresas a prosperar num panorama digital em rápida evolução. Com foco na excelência, integridade e colaboração, construímos parcerias duradouras através da compreensão das necessidades únicas de cada cliente e da oferta de suporte especializado em todas as fases. A nossa equipa dedica\-se a promover um ambiente de trabalho positivo e inclusivo, onde a contribuição de cada colaborador é valorizada, incentivando o crescimento contínuo, a aprendizagem e o sucesso partilhado. Junte\-se a nós e faça parte de uma organização apaixonada, impulsionada pela inovação e pela excelência.

**Sobre a vaga:**

Estamos a recrutar um(a) **AI Engineer** para integrar um projeto no setor da logística, com foco no desenvolvimento de soluções baseadas em Inteligência Artificial e Machine Learning.

Procuramos um profissional com experiência na criação e evolução de modelos de IA, capaz de transformar necessidades de negócio em soluções tecnológicas inovadoras, desde a criação de provas de conceito (PoC) até à implementação de produtos mínimos viáveis (MVP). Terá um papel relevante na exploração de novas abordagens de IA e na integração destas soluções em ambientes reais de negócio.

**Requisitos:**

* Licenciatura ou Mestrado em Informática, Ciência de Dados, Inteligência Artificial, Matemática ou área equivalente;
* Experiência profissional comprovada como **AI Engineer, Machine Learning Engineer ou função semelhante**;
* Conhecimentos sólidos de **Large Language Models (LLMs)**, **Machine Learning** e **Deep Learning**;
* Experiência com **frameworks e bibliotecas de IA**, como TensorFlow, PyTorch, Keras e LangChain;
* Bons conhecimentos de programação em **Python** e/ou **Java**;
* Experiência com **bibliotecas de manipulação, análise e visualização de dados**, como NumPy, pandas e Matplotlib;
* Conhecimentos de processamento de grandes volumes de dados e frameworks de computação distribuída, como Hadoop ou Spark, serão valorizados;
* Familiaridade com **plataformas cloud** (AWS, Azure ou Google Cloud) e serviços de Inteligência Artificial associados;
* Capacidade de traduzir necessidades de negócio em soluções técnicas eficazes;
* Excelentes competências de comunicação e trabalho em equipa;
* Forte capacidade analítica, atenção ao detalhe e orientação para a resolução de problemas;
* Proatividade, autonomia e interesse contínuo por novas tecnologias e tendências na área de IA.

Localização do trabalho: Remoto

**HORIEN Salt Battery Solutions,** nuovo brand commerciale di FZSoNick, è leader mondiale nella produzione e commercializzazione di sistemi di accumulo al nickel\-cloruro di sodio. Offre soluzioni di stoccaggio e backup dell'energia sicure e completamente sostenibili: dalle materie prime alla massima riciclabilità dei componenti, i nostri prodotti mirano a favorire il processo di decarbonizzazione verso un mondo più sostenibile.

 **HORIEN** è un gruppo industriale con stabilimenti produttivi e filiali commerciali in Italia, Svizzera, Stati Uniti, Messico, Brasile, Cina, Francia e Germania. Il gruppo è attivo nei settori dell’energia e della componentistica automotive ed è conosciuto per il suo impegno nel supportare la transizione verso nuovi sviluppi ed innovazioni.





**Posizione:**
--------------

Se con il tuo lavoro vuoi contribuire a rendere il mondo più sostenibile grazie ai prodotti che realizziamo, questa è l'azienda che fa per te!



Per la nostra sede di Stabio siamo alla ricerca di un **CUSTOMER QUALITY ENGINEER** che si occuperà delle seguenti attività:



* Gestione claim dei clienti;
* Coordinamento delle attività di troubleshooting;
* Guidare i team interfunzionali (Produzione, R\&D, Ingegneria di Processo) nell'analisi delle cause radice utilizzando strumenti standard di problem solving (5 Why, Diagramma di Ishikawa, ecc.);
* Proposta e validazione azioni correttive/preventive in collaborazione con le altre funzioni aziendali;
* Identificazione, raccolta e analisi statistica dei dati di qualità provenienti da campo;
* Supporto per miglioramento qualitativo dei prodotti esistenti e lo sviluppo di nuovi;
* Sviluppo di metriche e KPI relativi a guasti sul campo, Analisi Pareto, CAPA, MTBF, MTTR.
* Redazione della reportistica ad uso interno (management) ed esterno (clienti)
* Supporto alle altre funzioni aziendali nelle comunicazione verso i clienti.

**Requisiti:**
--------------

Il profilo ricercato è in possesso dei seguenti requisiti:



* Laurea triennale in Ingegneria o esperienza equivalente;
* Costituisce titolo preferenziale l’esperienza pregressa di Customer Quality in ambito industriale elettronico, elettrico o meccanico;
* Conoscenza della normative ISO 9001
* Conoscenza di base Lean Six Sigma, FMEA (Failure Modes \& Effects Analysis) e FMECA (Failure Modes, Effects, \& Criticality Analysis).
* Buona conoscenza della lingua inglese.

**Altre informazioni:**
-----------------------

* Lavoro in team e buona autonomia nel gestire i progetti assegnati, interfacciandosi con le altre funzioni aziendali e con i clienti;
* Disponibilità a viaggiare per brevi trasferte;
* Full time \- 40 ore settimanali

**Location:** Remote (EST Timezone)


**Department:** Engineering


**Employment Type:** Contract (B2B)


**Contract Length:** 6 months (with potential for extension)


### **About YLD:**



Our goal is to help our clients keep moving forward. We work with them to build the skills and capabilities they need to stay ahead of the competition, and we know our success only happens when they succeed. We're a team of curious, talented people, and we're committed to making YLD a place where great people want to work, grow, and stay.



We're a remote\-first consultancy specialising in software engineering, product design, and data. Our teams are based across London, Lisbon, and Porto, and we create digital solutions that continue to deliver value long after our work is done.


### **About the role:**



As a Forward Deployment Engineer at YLD, you'll embed with a banking client during a proof\-of\-value or implementation, turning their product requirements into working configuration on the client's platform. You'll sit between the client's regulated banking requirements and their live services, prove your work with captured evidence, and feed any platform friction back to the core engineering team.


### **Your day\-to\-day responsibilities can look like this:**


* Turn client requirements into transaction rules, event\-driven workflows, and configuration on the client's platform;
* Capture before/after evidence of your work so it can be reviewed and replayed by teammates or the client;
* Work closely with client teams in collaborative working sessions, explaining technical decisions and translating complex engineering concepts clearly;
* Investigate unfamiliar API contracts and client tooling independently to get integrations working;
* Debug issues that live in the client's platform rather than your own code, and file clean reproductions back to core engineering;
* Actively leverage AI\-powered tools and workflows to accelerate development, improve code quality, and drive engineering best practices.

### **Preferred Skills:**


* Hands\-on Python at minimum; Go is a nice\-to\-have;
* Experience with rules engines, workflow orchestration, or event\-driven systems (CEL, Temporal, or similar);
* Familiarity with Kafka or similar event streaming platforms;
* Experience in fintech, core banking, or regulated financial services environments;
* Prior core\-banking or ledger experience;
* Comfort working in an AI\-assisted or agentic development workflow.

### **You should apply if you are:**


* **Domain\-fluent:** you can talk banking and payments regulation and mechanics without needing a primer;
* **Proactive:** you take ownership and move things forward without waiting to be asked;
* **A strong communicator:** you express technical ideas clearly, in writing and in client\-facing conversations, with full professional fluency in English;
* **Confident presenting:** you bring a polished, engaged attitude to working sessions and stakeholder interactions;
* **Focused on quality:** you care about doing things properly and hold yourself to a high standard;
* **Pragmatic:** you make sensible trade\-offs and deliver results in ambiguous, fast\-moving environments;
* **A creative problem solver:** you approach hard engineering challenges with curiosity and ingenuity;
* **Collaborative:** you thrive on working within cross\-functional, distributed teams and value others' input.

### **What you'll get in return:**


* The chance to work with a forward\-thinking, ethical, and fun group of people and to develop and grow your skills in a fast\-moving business

### **Our typical recruitment process:**


* 1st Interview with a Talent Partner (30/45 mins)
* Technical Interview with our Senior Developers (1h30\)
* Final chat with our Client Partner (30/45 mins)


